\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy establishes mandatory requirements for the protection of privacy and data,
 including Criminal Justice Information (CJIS),
 Personally Identifiable Information (PII),
 and Protected Health Information (PHI),
 to ensure the confidentiality,
 integrity,
 and availability of Elko County information assets.
 This policy ensures compliance with applicable federal and state laws,
 regulations,
 and standards,
 with adherence verified through the audit process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Elko County Information Operations personnel,
 including all employees,
 elected officials,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 interns,
 and volunteers,
 who access,
 use,
 store,
 process,
 or transmit County information assets.
 This policy governs all systems,
 applications,
 and projects that process,
 store,
 or transmit County data,
 regardless of location or media.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Board of County Commissioners
\series default
:
 Shall approve the annual data governance plan submitted by the IT Director and review quarterly compliance reports on data protection incidents and remediation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director (LASO)
\series default
:
 Serves as the County’s primary authority for data security and privacy.
 Shall conduct quarterly compliance audits of data handling practices and ensure incident response capabilities meet statutory timelines.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Data Owners
\series default
:
 Shall classify data in accordance with this policy and review access privileges semi-annually.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All Personnel
\series default
:
 Shall strictly adhere to data handling procedures and report all suspected incidents immediately.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Failure to comply with this policy may result in disciplinary action,
 up to and including termination of employment,
 termination of contract,
 and civil or criminal prosecution.
 Exceptions to this policy must be documented in writing,
 formally approved by the IT Director and the District Attorney’s Office,
 and reviewed annually.
\end_layout

