\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1.
 Privacy by Design
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
New systems and major modifications to existing systems shall incorporate privacy protections into the system architecture during the initial design phase.
 Projects shall not proceed to development until a Privacy Impact Assessment (PIA) is approved by the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2.
 Data Collection and Minimization
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Only data strictly necessary for the performance of defined County business functions shall be collected.
 Determining the necessity of data collection shall be the responsibility of the designated Data Owner.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3.
 Access Control
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Access to non-public data shall be granted on a "Need-to-Know" and "Least Privilege" basis.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Access rights shall be reviewed in accordance with the recertification cadence defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Access shall be revoked upon termination of employment or contract in accordance with the timelines defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
