\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4.
 Encryption and Data Residency
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Data at Rest
\series default
:
 All PII,
 PHI,
 and CJIS data stored on mobile devices,
 laptops,
 or removable media must be encrypted.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Data in Transit
\series default
:
 All sensitive data transmitted over public networks must be encrypted using TLS 1.2 or higher.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Cryptographic Standards
\series default
:
 Encryption shall use FIPS 140-3 validated modules.
 Legacy FIPS 140-2 validated modules are permitted only until September 21,
 2026,
 after which they must be replaced.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Data Residency
\series default
:
 All County data must be stored within the physical borders of the United States.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5.
 Regulatory Alignment
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Elko County shall comply with NRS Chapter 603A and applicable federal privacy requirements.
 The IT Director shall maintain a register of applicable federal and state privacy laws and shall update this policy within 90 days of any new law taking effect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6.
 Data Retention
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Data shall be retained and disposed of in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and the applicable Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedules.
 Destruction of digital media must render the data irretrievable in accordance with NIST SP 800-88 Guidelines for Media Sanitization.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7.
 Data Classification Review
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Data Owners shall review data classification annually and document the results in writing to the IT Director.
 Data Owners shall update classification within 30 days when sensitivity changes and shall notify Information Operations Personnel in writing within 5 business days to implement updated safeguards.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.8.
 Data Security and Privacy Training
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
All personnel shall complete initial and annual security awareness and privacy training.
 Personnel must complete remedial training within 30 days of a major security event or policy violation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.9.
 Incident Reporting
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Suspected or confirmed data breaches,
 privacy incidents,
 or security events shall be reported to the IT Director (LASO) immediately upon discovery,
 not to exceed 1 hour,
 regardless of the time of day,
 day of week,
 or holiday status.
 This strict timeline is mandatory to comply with FBI CJIS reporting requirements and NRS breach notification statutes.
\end_layout

